Core Principles: The CIA Triad
The "CIA Triad" is the foundational model for cybersecurity: 

Confidentiality: Ensuring only authorized users can access sensitive data.
Integrity: Guaranteeing that data remains accurate and hasn't been tampered with.
Availability: Ensuring that systems and data are accessible when needed.

